  "texts": [
    "Panel A in Table 4 shows results for Python versus R. For commits that add new functions (Columns 1-3), our TWFE estimation shows that GitHub Copilot increases such commits by 0.8 per quarter, representing a 26.5% increase relative to the pre-treatment mean of 3.01 commits per quarter.",
    "The balanced TWFE",
    "shows an increase of 0.626 commits (20.8%), while the SDiD analysis shows a significant increase of 0.6 commits (19.9%).",
    "For commits that do not add new functions (Columns 4-6), we observe substantially larger effects: an increase of 6.016 commits per quarter in the TWFE model, representing a 39.1% increase relative to the pre-treatment mean of 15.38 commits.",
    "This effect remains robust in the balanced TWFE (4.870 commits, 31.7% increase) and SDiD analyses (4.226 commits, 27.5% increase)."
  ],
